134
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:45,844
Damn it, Cooley. Do it on three,
or go on the street.

135
00:17:50,290 --> 00:17:52,850
Silent night

136
00:17:53,730 --> 00:17:56,244
Are you telling me
Riggs is playing a game?

137
00:17:56,570 --> 00:17:59,767
Sure. He wants the cash.
But he'll come around.

138
00:18:00,090 --> 00:18:02,240
That's a very dangerous
attitude to take.

139
00:18:02,490 --> 00:18:06,961
Remember, his wife of 11 years
was just killed in a car accident.

140
00:18:07,330 --> 00:18:10,959
-He pulls his gun when he shouldn't.
-I know all about him.

141
00:18:11,210 --> 00:18:12,359
He's a tough bastard.

142
00:18:12,570 --> 00:18:15,687
He's on the edge. I'm telling you,
he may be psychotic.

143
00:18:15,890 --> 00:18:17,767
That's a bunch of psych bullshit.

144
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:20,723
You're making a mistake
by keeping him in the field.

145
00:18:21,050 --> 00:18:22,642
The man is suicidal.

146
00:18:22,890 --> 00:18:25,563
You're sure of that diagnosis?
You have no doubts?

147
00:18:25,850 --> 00:18:27,442
There are no absolutes in life.

148
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:30,158
End of discussion.
We're going to wait.

149
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:33,004
If he offs himself,
then we'll know I was wrong.

150
00:18:33,210 --> 00:18:36,407
You're making a mistake,
because if you're wrong...

151
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:44,882
Asshole!

152
00:18:45,410 --> 00:18:47,924
Roger, you're way behind the times.

153
00:18:48,170 --> 00:18:51,924
The guys in the 80s aren't tough.
They're sensitive people.

154
00:18:52,290 --> 00:18:55,168
They show emotions around women,
shit like that.

155
00:18:56,850 --> 00:18:58,329
I think I'm an 80s man.

156
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:00,003
How do you figure?

157
00:19:00,250 --> 00:19:01,603
Last night...

158
00:19:02,010 --> 00:19:03,921
...I cried in bed. How's that?

159
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:08,442
Were you with a woman?

160
00:19:08,890 --> 00:19:12,200
I was alone. Why do you think
I was crying? Merry Christmas.

161
00:19:12,450 --> 00:19:14,486
Sounds like an 80s man to me.

162
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:17,520
-News on the Hunsaker case.
-That was quick.

163
00:19:17,770 --> 00:19:21,046
So was the autopsy.
They're not calling it a suicide.

164
00:19:21,650 --> 00:19:25,404
Surprise, surprise. The coroner
found evidence she used barbiturates.

165
00:19:26,090 --> 00:19:27,523
Brilliant detective work.

166
00:19:27,730 --> 00:19:29,368
There were pills all over.

167
00:19:29,650 --> 00:19:31,880
Right. That's not the surprise.

168
00:19:32,210 --> 00:19:34,565
The surprise is the pills were doctored.

169
00:19:35,130 --> 00:19:37,519
The capsules were loaded with drain cleaner.

170
00:19:37,730 --> 00:19:38,879
She'd have died anyway.

171
00:19:39,090 --> 00:19:40,045
This case stinks.

172
00:19:40,290 --> 00:19:43,885
You know, you looked younger with the beard.

173
00:19:44,490 --> 00:19:45,809
Thanks, captain.

174
00:19:47,570 --> 00:19:48,605
You shaved the beard.

175
00:19:49,050 --> 00:19:50,244
Some detective.

176
00:19:50,770 --> 00:19:51,998
Two more things.

177
00:19:52,890 --> 00:19:55,245
The condition of the sheets indicates...

178
00:19:55,570 --> 00:19:58,448
...someone else was in bed with Amanda.
That's "A"

179
00:19:58,650 --> 00:19:59,560
What's "B"?

180
00:19:59,890 --> 00:20:02,962
