a new partner on this.

181
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,205
Partner again?

182
00:20:04,450 --> 00:20:07,760
Some cat on loan from Dope.
Real burnout, on the edge.

183
00:20:08,090 --> 00:20:09,079
Perfect.

184
00:20:11,610 --> 00:20:12,520
Gun!

185
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:20,808
Rog, meet your new partner.

186
00:20:24,450 --> 00:20:27,010
I'm too old for this shit.

187
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:33,485
There are those who say you're a good cop.

188
00:20:33,730 --> 00:20:35,049
I try.

189
00:20:35,730 --> 00:20:39,564
I heard about the little stunt yesterday.
Pretty heroic.

190
00:20:41,730 --> 00:20:43,322
I pulled your file.

191
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:47,245
Said you worked in the Phoenix
project in Vietnam. That right?

192
00:20:47,450 --> 00:20:50,283
Assassination stuff.
It's over, you know.

193
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:51,998
What is?

194
00:20:52,690 --> 00:20:53,645
The war.

195
00:20:53,890 --> 00:20:55,403
Yes, I know.

196
00:20:55,730 --> 00:20:57,322
Just thought I'd remind you.

197
00:20:59,370 --> 00:21:01,600
That's some serious shit you carry.

198
00:21:03,010 --> 00:21:04,602
Be my guest.

199
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:12,845
9mm Beretta. Takes 15 in the mag,
one up the pipe...

200
00:21:13,170 --> 00:21:16,606
...wide ejection port, no feed jams.

201
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:18,045
What have you got?

202
00:21:18,290 --> 00:21:19,359
Four-inch Smith.

203
00:21:20,850 --> 00:21:21,885
Six-shooter?

204
00:21:23,410 --> 00:21:24,923
A lot of old-timers carry those.

205
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:31,644
File also said you're heavy
into martial arts.

206
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:35,121
Tai chi and all that killer stuff.

207
00:21:35,450 --> 00:21:38,601
I suppose we have to register you
as a lethal weapon.

208
00:21:39,410 --> 00:21:43,119
Let's just cut the shit.
We both know why I was transferred.

209
00:21:43,330 --> 00:21:47,482
Everybody thinks I'm suicidal,
so nobody wants to work with me.

210
00:21:47,730 --> 00:21:50,085
Some think I'm faking
to draw psycho pension...

211
00:21:50,330 --> 00:21:54,118
...so nobody wants to work with me.
Basically, I'm fucked.

212
00:21:54,330 --> 00:21:55,319
Guess what?

213
00:21:55,730 --> 00:21:57,129
I don't want to work with you.

214
00:21:57,330 --> 00:21:58,160
Then don't.

215
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:02,363
Ain't got no choice.
Looks like we both got fucked.

216
00:22:02,570 --> 00:22:03,480
Terrific.

217
00:22:07,530 --> 00:22:09,202
God hates me, is what it is.

218
00:22:10,290 --> 00:22:12,406
Hate Him back. It works for me.

219
00:22:29,770 --> 00:22:32,125
-Good afternoon, Mr. Mendez.
-How you doing?

220
00:22:32,370 --> 00:22:33,564
Did you pat him down?

221
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:36,370
-We went through this already.
-Go through it again.

222
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:37,805
Who are you?

223
00:22:38,170 --> 00:22:41,003
That's hardly important,
but you may call me Mr. Joshua.

224
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:42,239
Let's go.

225
00:22:42,450 --> 00:22:44,680
Great, swell. Mr. Joshua, huh?

226
00:22:49,250 --> 00:22:51,081
General, Mr. Mendez is here.

227
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:58,285
You call this music? I can get
a better band for half the price.

228
00:22:58,610 --> 00:23:02,125
I don't want to hear any of this shit.
Let's get it right.

229
00:23:04,290 --> 00:23:06,281
Mr. Mendez, how are you?

230
00:23:06,690 --> 00:23:07,759
I'm fine.

231
00:23:08,410 --> 00:23:10,765
